    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion criteria:

          -  Alport syndrome diagnosis (clinical and/or histopathologic and/or genetic diagnosis,
             per subject's physician and/or genotyping)

          -  Physically able to provide a single first-morning urine sample of at least 30 mL

        Exclusion criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of chronic kidney disease

          -  Receiving chronic phosphate-lowering therapy or erythropoietin therapy

          -  Ongoing chronic hemodialysis therapy and/or renal transplant recipient

          -  Nephrotic-range proteinuria: spot urine protein-to-creatinine ratio â‰¥ 3 on at least 2
             of the last 3 clinical assessments Other protocol-defined inclusion/exclusion criteria
             may apply
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
